<TITLE> HC upholds death for 9 in Kazi Arif killing </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 5 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court Tuesday upheld death sentences of nine people and acquitted one person facing death after being convicted for the killing of JSD leader Kazi Arif Ahmed. The High Court also acquitted 13 others who were convicted and sentenced to life imprisonment. A High court bench of justices AKM Fazlur Rahman and ATM Fazle Kabir issued the order after concluding a joint hearing of an appeal by the defence and a death reference by the state. Five people, including Kazi Arif, JSD Kushtia district president Lokman Hossain and general secretary Yakub Ali were killed during a Jatiya Samajtantrik Dal rally in Kushtia in 1999. Sub-inspector of police Humayun Kabir filed a case with Doulatpur Police Station the same day. A total of 28 people were made accused in the first and second chargesheets though there were no names in the original FIR. On Aug 30, 2004, additional sessions judge for Kushtia, Fazlur Rahman issued death sentences to 10 people and sentenced 13 to life imprisonment after recording testimony from 41 witnesses. One accused was acquitted in the case. Of the remaining four, two died and the HC dropped two from the case. bdnew
